---
import MainLayout from "../../layouts/MainLayout.astro";
---

<MainLayout>
  <!-- MAIN CONTENT -->
  <main class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 py-8">
    <!-- HERO SECTION -->
    <section class="mb-16">
      <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
        <div class="text-center mb-8">
          <span
            class="text-purple-600 font-bold text-sm uppercase tracking-wider"
            >Programs</span
          >
          <h1
            class="text-5xl md:text-6xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-2 mb-4 leading-tight"
          >
            Handler Coaching Course
          </h1>
          <div class="flex justify-center gap-3 mb-6">
            <span class="tag">5-6 Sessions</span>
            <span class="tag">You Become the Trainer</span>
            <span class="tag">Lifetime Skills</span>
          </div>
          <p
            class="text-xl md:text-2xl text-gray-700 max-w-4xl mx-auto leading-relaxed"
          >
            This isn't about training your dog—it's about <strong
              >training you</strong
            >. Learn the skills, timing, and techniques to become your dog's
            calm, clear leader. Build <strong
              >real-world reliability through structure and consistency</strong
            >—not force.
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-600 mt-4">
            <strong>Serving Bassett & Southwest Virginia</strong> • <a
              href="tel:+12762292625"
              class="text-purple-600 hover:underline font-semibold"
              >(276) 229-2625</a
            >
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Quick CTA Buttons -->
        <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center mt-8">
          <a
            href="#what-youll-learn"
            class="bg-purple-600 hover:bg-purple-700 text-white font-bold px-8 py-4 rounded-full text-lg transition transform hover:scale-105 text-center"
          >
            See What You'll Learn
          </a>
          <a
            href="https://leashlegacyk9.com/contact/"
            class="bg-gray-900 hover:bg-gray-800 text-white font-bold px-8 py-4 rounded-full text-lg border-2 border-gray-900 transition text-center"
          >
            Schedule a Consultation
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- WHAT IS THIS PROGRAM -->
    <section class="mb-20 bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-xl p-8 md:p-12">
      <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-8 text-center">
        What Is the Handler Coaching Course?
      </h2>

      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <div
          class="bg-gradient-to-br from-purple-50 to-indigo-50 p-8 rounded-xl border-2 border-purple-200 mb-8"
        >
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-800 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            The <strong>Handler Coaching Course</strong> is a structured coaching
            system designed to teach you how dogs actually learn, how behavior forms,
            and how consistency—not force—creates reliability.
          </p>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-800 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            This is <strong>not a quick-fix course</strong>. This is intensive,
            hands-on coaching where <em>you</em> learn to train your dog. Your dog
            already knows how to be a dog. Now it's time for you to learn how to be
            a calm, clear leader they can trust.
          </p>
          <p class="text-xl font-bold text-purple-700 text-center mt-6">
            "If you commit to the process, your dog will meet you there."
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-8">
          <div class="bg-green-50 border-l-4 border-green-500 p-6 rounded-lg">
            <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3 text-lg">
              ✅ This Course IS:
            </h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
              <li>• Handler-focused coaching</li>
              <li>• Built around structure and timing</li>
              <li>• Adapted to each dog-handler team</li>
              <li>• Grounded in real-life scenarios</li>
              <li>• Focused on nervous system regulation</li>
              <li>• Built on consistency and clarity</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-red-50 border-l-4 border-red-500 p-6 rounded-lg">
            <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3 text-lg">
              ❌ This Course IS NOT:
            </h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
              <li>• A one-size-fits-all program</li>
              <li>• A shortcut to obedience</li>
              <li>• A replacement for daily structure</li>
              <li>• A punishment-based system</li>
              <li>• A guarantee of perfection</li>
              <li>• A passive class where you watch</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div
          class="bg-yellow-50 border-2 border-yellow-300 p-6 rounded-xl text-center"
        >
          <p class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900">
            <strong>Remember:</strong> Dogs don't fail this course. <span
              class="text-purple-700">Inconsistency does.</span
            >
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- PROGRAM STRUCTURE -->
    <section class="mb-20">
      <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-12 text-center">
        Program Structure: Adaptive by Design
      </h2>

      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <div
          class="bg-gradient-to-r from-purple-50 to-blue-50 p-8 rounded-xl border-2 border-purple-200 mb-8"
        >
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-800 leading-relaxed mb-6">
            The Handler Coaching Course is structured to build on itself—each
            session lays the foundation for the next. This is <strong
              >not a rigid, cookie-cutter program</strong
            >. Your training plan evolves based on your dog's responses, your
            consistency between sessions, and the progress you make together.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
          <div
            class="feature-card bg-white p-6 rounded-xl shadow-md border-t-4 border-purple-500"
          >
            <div class="text-4xl mb-4">📅</div>
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Sessions</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">
              Approximately 45 minutes of intensive coaching per session. 5–6
              classes total, scheduled progressively over several weeks.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div
            class="feature-card bg-white p-6 rounded-xl shadow-md border-t-4 border-blue-500"
          >
            <div class="text-4xl mb-4">📈</div>
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Progression</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">
              Each session builds on the last—we do not advance until the
              foundation is solid. Learn timing, principles, and real-world
              application.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div
            class="feature-card bg-white p-6 rounded-xl shadow-md border-t-4 border-green-500"
          >
            <div class="text-4xl mb-4">🔄</div>
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Variables</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">
              Your program evolves based on your dog's responses and your
              consistency at home. We adjust, troubleshoot, and adapt to your
              team.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- WHAT YOU'LL LEARN -->
    <section
      id="what-youll-learn"
      class="mb-20 bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-xl p-8 md:p-12"
    >
      <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-8 text-center">
        What You'll Learn
      </h2>

      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 text-center mb-12">
          This program is designed to give you the <strong
            >skills, knowledge, and confidence</strong
          > to train your own dog. Here's what we'll cover:
        </p>

        <div class="space-y-6">
          <!-- Learning Module 1 -->
          <div class="bg-purple-50 p-6 rounded-xl border-l-4 border-purple-500">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">
              📚 Foundational Training Principles & Timing
            </h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700">
              Learn how dogs process information, how to use markers and rewards
              effectively, and how to communicate clearly.
            </p>
          </div>

          <!-- Learning Module 2 -->
          <div class="bg-blue-50 p-6 rounded-xl border-l-4 border-blue-500">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">
              🎯 How to Teach Sit, Down, Place, and Recall
            </h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700">
              Master the core obedience commands with proper technique and
              timing.
            </p>
          </div>

          <!-- Learning Module 3 -->
          <div class="bg-green-50 p-6 rounded-xl border-l-4 border-green-500">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">
              🚶 Loose-Leash Walking with Real-World Application
            </h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700">
              Build structured walking that holds up around distractions—not
              just in your living room.
            </p>
          </div>

          <!-- Learning Module 4 -->
          <div class="bg-yellow-50 p-6 rounded-xl border-l-4 border-yellow-500">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">
              👁️ Building Engagement and Focus
            </h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700">
              Teach your dog to pay attention to you, even when the environment
              is chaotic.
            </p>
          </div>

          <!-- Learning Module 5 -->
          <div class="bg-red-50 p-6 rounded-xl border-l-4 border-red-500">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">
              🧠 Impulse Control Exercises and Decision-Making
            </h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700">
              Help your dog learn to calm their nervous system and make better
              choices.
            </p>
          </div>

          <!-- Learning Module 6 -->
          <div class="bg-indigo-50 p-6 rounded-xl border-l-4 border-indigo-500">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">
              📡 E-Collar Fundamentals and Proper Introduction
            </h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700">
              If appropriate for your dog, learn humane e-collar use,
              conditioning, and communication.
            </p>
          </div>

          <!-- Learning Module 7 -->
          <div class="bg-orange-50 p-6 rounded-xl border-l-4 border-orange-500">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">
              🔧 Troubleshooting Common Mistakes
            </h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700">
              Learn to read your dog's body language, adjust on the fly, and fix
              errors before they become habits.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- NON-NEGOTIABLE EXPECTATIONS -->
    <section
      class="mb-20 bg-gradient-to-r from-red-50 to-orange-50 py-16 px-4 rounded-2xl"
    >
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-8 text-center">
          Non-Negotiable Expectations
        </h2>

        <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-xl shadow-lg mb-8">
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 text-center mb-8 italic">
            "This isn't about being strict. It's about being clear."
          </p>

          <p class="text-gray-800 mb-8">
            These standards protect your progress and your dog's clarity.
            They're not optional.
          </p>

          <div class="space-y-6">
            <!-- Expectation 1 -->
            <div class="border-l-4 border-purple-500 pl-6 py-2">
              <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
                1. One Primary Handler During Training Sessions
              </h3>
              <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">
                Your dog needs consistency. If multiple people handle your dog
                differently, progress will stall. During training sessions, one
                person leads. Family members are welcome to observe, but the
                primary handler must be the same person every week.
              </p>
            </div>

            <!-- Expectation 2 -->
            <div class="border-l-4 border-blue-500 pl-6 py-2">
              <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
                2. Training Methods Must Stay Consistent with LLK9 Coaching at
                Home
              </h3>
              <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">
                What we build in sessions only works if you reinforce it at
                home. If you're using one method with me and a different
                approach on your own, your dog will become confused. Consistency
                is everything. If you're not ready to commit to the LLK9
                approach at home, this program won't work.
              </p>
            </div>

            <!-- Expectation 3 -->
            <div class="border-l-4 border-green-500 pl-6 py-2">
              <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
                3. Homework is Required. Missed Reps = Delayed Results.
              </h3>
              <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">
                You'll receive homework after every session—short, focused
                practice assignments that reinforce what we worked on. These
                aren't optional. If you skip homework, your dog won't generalize
                the training, and we'll spend the next session re-teaching
                instead of progressing. Expect to practice 10–15 minutes, twice
                per day.
              </p>
            </div>

            <!-- Expectation 4 -->
            <div class="border-l-4 border-yellow-500 pl-6 py-2">
              <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
                4. Be On Time and Prepared
              </h3>
              <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">
                Sessions are 45 minutes. If you're late, we lose valuable
                coaching time. Bring your dog's leash, collar, any training
                tools we've discussed, and a focused mindset. Leave distractions
                (phones, other obligations) behind.
              </p>
            </div>

            <!-- Expectation 5 -->
            <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-6 py-2">
              <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
                5. Communicate Challenges—Don't Hide Them
              </h3>
              <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">
                If something isn't working at home, tell me. If your dog
                regressed, struggled, or you're confused about a technique—tell
                me. I can't help you fix what I don't know about. This program
                only works if we're honest about where you are.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div
          class="bg-yellow-50 border-2 border-yellow-300 p-6 rounded-xl text-center"
        >
          <p class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900">
            These expectations exist to ensure your success. If you're not ready
            to commit, let's discuss whether this program is the right fit.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- PROGRAM INCLUDES -->
    <section class="mb-20">
      <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-12 text-center">
        What's Included in Your Program
      </h2>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
        <div
          class="feature-card bg-white p-6 rounded-xl shadow-md border-t-4 border-purple-500"
        >
          <div class="text-4xl mb-4">🎓</div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
            5–6 In-Person Coaching Classes
          </h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">
            Approximately 45 minutes each, scheduled progressively over several
            weeks. Each session builds on the last.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div
          class="feature-card bg-white p-6 rounded-xl shadow-md border-t-4 border-blue-500"
        >
          <div class="text-4xl mb-4">📋</div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
            Customized Training Plan
          </h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">
            Tailored to your dog and your goals. Your program evolves based on
            your progress and consistency.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div
          class="feature-card bg-white p-6 rounded-xl shadow-md border-t-4 border-green-500"
        >
          <div class="text-4xl mb-4">📖</div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
            Take-Home Training Materials
          </h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">
            Homework assignments, written guides, and practice logs to reinforce
            what you learn in each session.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div
          class="feature-card bg-white p-6 rounded-xl shadow-md border-t-4 border-yellow-500"
        >
          <div class="text-4xl mb-4">👨‍🏫</div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
            Direct Trainer Feedback
          </h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">
            Live coaching during each session with personalized technique
            correction, timing help, and troubleshooting.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div
          class="feature-card bg-white p-6 rounded-xl shadow-md border-t-4 border-red-500"
        >
          <div class="text-4xl mb-4">📧</div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
            Email Support Between Classes
          </h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">
            If you're stuck or have questions between sessions, reach out—don't
            wait until the next class.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div
          class="feature-card bg-white p-6 rounded-xl shadow-md border-t-4 border-indigo-500"
        >
          <div class="text-4xl mb-4">🌍</div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
            Real-World Training Scenarios
          </h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">
            We train for reliability under pressure—not just perfect reps in a
            quiet room.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div
        class="mt-8 bg-gradient-to-r from-purple-50 to-blue-50 border-2 border-purple-200 p-6 rounded-xl text-center"
      >
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-800">
          <strong
            >You become the trainer. We coach you every step of the way so your
            dog learns from you, not just in class.</strong
          >
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- INVESTMENT -->
    <section class="mb-20 bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-xl p-8 md:p-12">
      <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-8 text-center">
        Investment & What's Included
      </h2>

      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <div
          class="bg-gradient-to-br from-purple-50 to-indigo-50 p-8 rounded-xl border-2 border-purple-300 mb-8 text-center"
        >
          <div class="text-5xl font-bold text-purple-600 mb-4">$400</div>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700">Full Handler Coaching Course</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border-2 border-gray-200 p-6 rounded-xl">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4 text-center">
            This investment includes:
          </h3>
          <ul class="space-y-3 text-gray-700">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-purple-600 font-bold text-xl">✓</span>
              <span
                >5–6 in-person coaching classes (approximately 45 minutes each)</span
              >
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-purple-600 font-bold text-xl">✓</span>
              <span
                >Customized training plan tailored to your dog and goals</span
              >
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-purple-600 font-bold text-xl">✓</span>
              <span
                >Take-home training materials, homework assignments, and written
                guides</span
              >
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-purple-600 font-bold text-xl">✓</span>
              <span>Direct trainer feedback during each session</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-purple-600 font-bold text-xl">✓</span>
              <span>Email support between classes</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-purple-600 font-bold text-xl">✓</span>
              <span
                >Progressive skill building with personalized technique
                correction</span
              >
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div
          class="mt-8 bg-purple-50 border-2 border-purple-300 p-6 rounded-xl text-center"
        >
          <p class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900">
            Invest in yourself—and build a training foundation that lasts a
            lifetime with your dog.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- TRAINING PHILOSOPHY -->
    <section class="mb-20">
      <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-12 text-center">
        Our Training Philosophy
      </h2>

      <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
        <div class="bg-white p-10 rounded-2xl shadow-xl mb-8">
          <div class="text-center mb-8">
            <p class="text-3xl font-bold text-purple-600 mb-4">
              "Calm is trained, not expected."
            </p>
            <p class="text-lg text-gray-700">
              We reject dominance myths, intimidation tactics, and any approach
              that creates learned helplessness or fear.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3 text-lg">We Believe:</h3>
              <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
                <li>• Calm is trained, not expected</li>
                <li>• Structure creates confidence—chaos creates anxiety</li>
                <li>
                  • Nervous system regulation comes before obedience demands
                </li>
                <li>• Consistency beats intensity every time</li>
                <li>• Dogs follow leadership, not force</li>
                <li>
                  • Real-world reliability matters more than sterile obedience
                  drills
                </li>
                <li>• Handler education is as important as dog training</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div>
              <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3 text-lg">
                How We Train:
              </h3>
              <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
                <li>• Positive reinforcement as the foundation</li>
                <li>• Clear communication and calm leadership</li>
                <li>• Short, focused sessions to avoid burnout</li>
                <li>• Dogs are worked <em>with</em>, not overwhelmed</li>
                <li>
                  • Teaching dogs <strong>how to learn</strong>, not just what
                  to do
                </li>
                <li>
                  • Training tools introduced with humane use and handler
                  education
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div
          class="bg-gradient-to-r from-purple-50 to-indigo-50 p-8 rounded-xl border-2 border-purple-200"
        >
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 text-center">
            The goal is never compliance through fear. The goal is a dog who
            understands what's being asked and chooses to respond.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- WHAT TO BRING -->
    <section class="mb-20">
      <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-12 text-center">
        What to Bring to Each Session
      </h2>

      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-xl shadow-lg">
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6 text-center">
            Come prepared so we can make the most of every session:
          </p>

          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
            <div class="bg-purple-50 p-6 rounded-lg">
              <h3 class="font-bold text-purple-900 mb-3">Essential Items:</h3>
              <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700 text-sm">
                <li>
                  • Your dog on a standard leash and flat collar or martingale
                </li>
                <li>
                  • Any training tools we've discussed (e-collar, long line,
                  treats, etc.)
                </li>
                <li>
                  • Questions or challenges you've encountered during homework
                </li>
                <li>
                  • A notebook or phone for taking notes (optional but
                  recommended)
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-blue-50 p-6 rounded-lg">
              <h3 class="font-bold text-blue-900 mb-3">Your Mindset:</h3>
              <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700 text-sm">
                <li>• A focused mindset—leave distractions behind</li>
                <li>• Ready to learn and practice hands-on</li>
                <li>• Open to feedback and technique correction</li>
                <li>• Prepared to ask questions and communicate honestly</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div
            class="mt-6 bg-yellow-50 border-l-4 border-yellow-500 p-4 rounded"
          >
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
              <strong>Note:</strong> If your dog has specific dietary restrictions,
              bring their preferred training treats. Otherwise, we'll provide what's
              needed during sessions.
            </p>
          </div>
